Class Deals

  • java.lang.Object
    • common.Deals
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Deals
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The Deals class represents a deal offered by the company. It holds information about the deal such as the deal ID, name, discount, description, type, area, status, start date, and end date. It also implements Serializable interface to make it possible to save the object's state.

        public Deals(java.lang.String DealName,
             float Discount,
             java.lang.String Description,
             java.lang.String Type,
             java.lang.String Area,
             java.lang.String StatusString,
             java.lang.String active)
        Constructor for the Deals class that takes in the deal name, discount, description, type, area, status, and active status as arguments.
        Parameters:
        DealName - The name of the deal.
        Discount - The percentage of the discount offered by the deal.
        Description - A brief description of the deal.
        Type - The category of the deal (Drink, Snacks, All).
        Area - The area of the deal (North, South, UAE).
        StatusString - The status of the deal(Approved, Not Approved) in string format.
        active - The active status of the deal (active or not active).
